title.narrative: WAPP APL4 (Phase 1) - C te d'Ivoire, Sierra Leone, Liberia, and Guinea Power System Re-development

description.narrative: The revised PDOs for the WAPP CLSG Power Interconnection are to: (a) reduce the cost of electricity supply at the utility level for Liberia and Sierra Leone and (b) increase the amount of electricity traded among all the participating countries. The Development Objective of the WAPP TA is to increase the technical integration of the WAPP network.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article IV | Description :Finance Agreement: CR 5110-LR | Description :The Association may suspend disbursementsunder the Credit if the Guinea Financing Agreement shall have failed to become effective. | Due Date :31-Jul-2015

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :Not later than six months after effectiveness date; (i) Set up an audit committeeunder TOR and with a composition satisfactory to the Association to follow up with management on any issues raised in the annualaudits, thereby ensuring they are properly addressed; and (ii) develop an anti-fraud and anti-corruption policy satisfactory to theAssociation to handle any fraud and corruption cases. | Due Date :30-Mar-2015
Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall cause the RTC to acquire and install a suitable accountinginformation system for the project. | Due Date :30-Mar-2015

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall cause the RTC to collect, compile and furnish to the Associationreports on the status of compliance with the Environmental and Social Impact Assessments (ESIAs), the Environmental and SocialManagement Plans (ESMPs), and the Resettlement Action Plans (RAPs) for the participating countries. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall cause the RTC to prepare and furnish to the Association as part ofthe project report not later than forty-five(45) days after the end of each quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for theproject covering the quarter, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall cause the RTC to recruit a qualified and experienced internalauditor and an accounts officer on the basis of terms of reference and experience satisfactory to the Association and to acquireand install an accounting information system for theProject. | Due Date :30-Mar-2015

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the RTC conclude with the WAPP a Control AreaAgreement in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :31-Jan-2016

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the RTC employ an operations and maintenancecontractor under terms of reference and with experience and qualifications satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :31-Jul-2019

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall exercise its rights and carry out its obligations under theSubsidiary Credit implementation agreement in such manner as to protect the interests of the Recipient and the Association and toaccomplish the purposes of the Credit. Except as the Association shall otherwise agree, the Recipient shall not assign, amend,abrogate or waive the SCA or any of its provisions. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall require the RTC to carry out the project with due diligence andefficiency and in accordance with sound technical, economic, energy, financial, managerial, environmental and social standards andpractices satisfactory to the Association, including in accordance with the provisions of the ESMPs and the RAPs and pursuant tothe RTC PIM and Anti-Corruption guidelines applicable. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall require the Regional Transmission Company (RTC), except as theAssociation shall otherwise agree, to maintain adebt service coverage ratio of at least 1.3 under terms and conditions that havebeen agreed upon with the Association. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :CR 5110-LR | Description :The Recipient shall take all action required on its behalf to ensure that the projectis implemented in accordance with the provisions of the Liberia Environmental and Social Impact Assessment (Liberia ESIA), theLiberia Environmental and Social Management Plan (Liberia ESMP), and the Liberia Resettlement Action Plan (Liberia RAP), all in amanner satisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
